PROBLEM :
Write a program to reverse the elements in an single dimensional array

HOW I IMPLEMENTED THIS ?
First read the elements into array.
Then take two pointers start for pointing to starting index of array and end for pointing to last ending of the array.
Use while loop, for every start<end swap the elemets at start index with end endex and vice versa.

ALGORITHM :
rvereseArray(int arr[],int start, int end)
{
  int temp;
  while (start < end)
  {
    temp = arr[start];
    arr[start] = arr[end];
    arr[end] = temp;
    start++;
    end--;
  }
}


TEST CASE 1:
  INPUT :
    Enter array size
    5
    Enter elements into array
    1 2 3 4 5
  OUTPUT :
    Actual array is
    1 2 3 4 5
    Reversed array is
    5 4 3 2 1 
    
    
TEST CASE 2:
  INPUT :
    Enter array size
    1
    Enter elements into array
    13
  OUTPUT :
    Actual array is
    13
    Reversed array is
    13
    
    
 TEST CASE 3:
   INPUT :
     Enter array size
     0
     Enter elements into array
                                     // NO ELEMENTS IN THE ARRAY
   OUTPUT :
     Actual array is

     Reversed array is
                                      //NO OUTPUT
